cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: The paper deals with the undecidability of MSO on $\omega$-words with additional predicates, which is a topic in logic and automata theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves formal languages and automata, which suggests categories such as cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of second-order predicates and the connection to undecidability of satisfiability suggests categories such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
